+# Deep Audit Fixes Plan
+
+## Overview
+This document outlines the actionable steps to resolve the critical architectural and cost-optimization issues identified during the deep audit of the CSMS codebase.
+
+## Objective
+To enforce the Clean Architecture patterns, implement robust offline-first synchronization using Hive, and rigorously optimize Firestore interactions to prevent quota exhaustion on the Firebase Spark (free) plan.
+
+## Tasks
+
+### Phase 1: Robust Offline-First Cache (Hive TypeAdapters)
+Currently, data is being cached as dynamic Maps, bypassing Hive's type safety and performance benefits.
+- [ ] **Annotate Models:** Ensure `StudentModel`, `ServantModel`, `TeamModel`, and any other core entities are annotated with `@HiveType` and `@HiveField`.
+- [ ] **Generate Adapters:** Run `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` to generate the `.g.dart` adapter files.
+- [ ] **Register Adapters:** Update `main.dart` or the DI initialization sequence to register all generated TypeAdapters (including `SyncStatusAdapter`) using `Hive.registerAdapter()` before any Hive boxes are opened.
+- [ ] **Refactor Datasources:** Update `StudentLocalDatasource` and other local datasources to utilize strongly-typed `Box<T>` instead of `Box<dynamic>`, streamlining cache reads and writes.
+
+### Phase 2: Firestore Cost Optimization (Eliminate Streams)
+The current usage of `.snapshots()` creates persistent listeners that continuously consume document reads, risking rapid quota exhaustion.
+- [ ] **Refactor `attendance_mark_repository.dart`:** Replace `.snapshots()` with `.get(const GetOptions(source: Source.serverAndCache))`.
+- [ ] **Refactor `attendance_repository.dart`:** Replace `.snapshots()` with `.get()`.
+- [ ] **Refactor `attendance_session_repository.dart`:** Replace `.snapshots()` with `.get()`.
+- [ ] **Refactor `team_repository.dart`:** Replace `.snapshots()` with `.get()`.
+- [ ] **Update BLoCs:** Modify corresponding BLoCs to fetch data discretely on initialization or via explicit pull-to-refresh events, relying on the `SyncService` for background updates rather than active streams.
+
+### Phase 3: Query & N+1 Optimization
+- [ ] **Audit Data Fetches:** Review all repository methods that fetch lists of items (e.g., fetching students for a specific team).
+- [ ] **Implement Batching:** Ensure that data fetching leverages `whereIn` queries or batched reads rather than iterating and fetching documents individually.
+
+---
+*Generated by Gemini CLI after CSMS Deep Audit.*
